This paper discusses a resource scheduler for a multi-tenant clustered environment, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper specifically focuses on the Apache Mesos framework, which is an operating system for data centers, making cs.OS another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the Dominant Resource Fairness (DRF) policy, which is a scheduling policy used in distributed systems, making cs.SY a possible sub-category. The paper also discusses the impact of resource demand and queue wait time on fairness, which could fall under the sub-categories of Networked Systems (cs.NI) and Performance (cs.PF).
